-- Toys ‘R’ Us Owners Considering Adding Equity, Sunday Times Says
-- B y   L u c y   M e a k i n
-- 2012-04-29T09:12:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-29/toys-r-us-owners-considering-adding-equity-sunday-times-says.html
The owners of Toys ‘R’ Us are
considering options, including adding new equity and extending
debt repayment deadlines, before 400 million pounds ($651
billion) of loans on its British operations are due, the  Sunday
Times  reported.  KKR & Co., Bain Capital LLC and Vornado Realty Trust are
close to appointing Cairn Capital Ltd. as adviser, the London-
based newspaper said, without saying where it got the
information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucy Meakin in London at 
